The genus
Plusiocampa
has been divided into four subgenera based on two characters: the presence of the femoral dorsal macrosetae (
Condé 1955 a
;
Paclt 1957
;
Sendra & Weber 2018
) and the number of tibial ventral macrosetae (
Bareth & Condé 1984
). Based on these synapomorphies and other characters, the following taxonomic key is proposed for the current five subgenera and 69 species.
